      <DefaultText>Taunt him just a little.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>Lord [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url],

My investigation into [url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url] and [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url] will require any and all resources I can acquire.

Perhaps something additional could be directed my way. It would certainly make my job easier.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>Lord [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url],

I feel my efforts would be well-spent talking to the soldiers of the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url]. While I doubt those guilty of treason would be forthcoming with the truth, criminals often let their defenses down amongst friends.

If you have it within your capacity to speak to members of the Chorus or send good word on my behalf, any help from you with the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] could assist my inquest.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>Lord [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url],

What of the growing rebellion that occurs during this time of infighting? Who will silence the growing voice of insurrection?</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>Lord [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url],

I will endeavor to conduct a most thorough inquiry on the matter. I will determine if one or both are guilty of treachery, or if the fight between the two was instigated by some third force.

As always, I am your twin hands of justice and accord.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>Well hello [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url],

My understanding, which - in all fairness - is limited to what you have taught me, is that you are the Archon responsible for keeping [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' Peace. [url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url] and [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url] might claim the ground, but yours is the burden of pacification.

So instead of asking me to investigate some treachery, let's just call it what it is - I'm helping you cover for your inability to notice dissension in your allies until it's too late.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
